namespace Magnum {
/** @page examples-arcball-camera ArcBall Camera
@brief ArcBall Camera example.
@m_since_latest_{examples}

@m_footernavigation

This is an implementation of [Ken Shoemake's arcball camera](https://www.talisman.org/~erlkonig/misc/shoemake92-arcball.pdf) with smooth navigation feature. Using arcball, the camera control is more accurate and consistent.

@image html arcball-camera.png width=400px

@section examples-arcball-camera-controls Controls

-   @m_class{m-label m-default} **Left mouse drag** rotate the camera
-   @m_class{m-label m-default} **Right mouse drag** translate the camera
-   @m_class{m-label m-default} **Middle mouse scrolling** zoom the camera in/out
-   @m_class{m-label m-default} **R** reset the camera to its original transformation
-   @m_class{m-label m-default} **L** toggle lagging (smooth camera navigation)
-   @m_class{m-label m-default} **Up/Down/Left/Right arrows** translate the camera
-   @m_class{m-label m-default} **+/-** zoom the camera

@section examples-arcball-camera-credits Credits

This example was originally contributed by [Nghia Truong](https://github.com/ttnghia).

@section examples-arcball-camera-source Source

Full source code is linked below and also available in the
[magnum-examples GitHub repository](https://github.com/mosra/magnum-examples/tree/master/src/arcball-camera).

-   @ref arcball-camera/CMakeLists.txt "CMakeLists.txt"
-   @ref arcball-camera/ArcBall.h "ArcBall.h"
-   @ref arcball-camera/ArcBall.cpp "ArcBall.cpp"
-   @ref arcball-camera/ArcBallCamera.h "ArcBallCamera.h"
-   @ref arcball-camera/ArcBallCameraExample.cpp "ArcBallCameraExample.cpp"

